<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="TreeMenu.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PhpDocumentor/HTML_TreeMenu-1.1.2/TreeMenu.php"><scope doc="HTML_TreeMenu Class&#10;&#10;A simple couple of PHP classes and some not so simple&#10;Jabbascript which produces a tree menu. In IE this menu&#10;is dynamic, with branches being collapsable. In IE5+ the&#10;status of the collapsed/open branches persists across page&#10;refreshes.In any other browser the tree is static. Code is&#10;based on work of Harald Radi.&#10;&#10;Usage.&#10;&#10;After installing the package, copy the example php script to&#10;your servers document root. Also place the TreeMenu.js and the&#10;images folder in the same place. Running the script should&#10;then produce the tree.&#10;&#10;Thanks go to Chip Chapin (http://www.chipchapin.com) for many&#10;excellent ideas and improvements.&#10;&#10;@author  Richard Heyes &lt;richard@php.net&gt;&#10;@author  Harald Radi &lt;harald.radi@nme.at&gt;&#10;@access  public&#10;@package HTML_TreeMenu" ilk="class" line="67" lineend="99" name="HTML_TreeMenu"><variable citdl="array" doc="Indexed array of subnodes&#10;@var array" line="73" name="items" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor&#10;&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="80" lineend="83" name="HTML_TreeMenu" signature="HTML_TreeMenu()" /><scope doc="This function adds an item to the the tree.&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param  object $node The node to add. This object should be&#10;                     a HTML_TreeNode object.&#10;@return object       Returns a reference to the new node inside&#10;                     the tree." ilk="function" line="94" lineend="98" name="addItem" returns="object" signature="object &amp;addItem(object &amp; $node)"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="94" name="node" /></scope></scope><scope doc="HTML_TreeNode class&#10;&#10;This class is supplementary to the above and provides a way to&#10;add nodes to the tree. A node can have other nodes added to it. &#10;&#10;@author  Richard Heyes &lt;richard@php.net&gt;&#10;@author  Harald Radi &lt;harald.radi@nme.at&gt;&#10;@access  public&#10;@package HTML_TreeMenu" ilk="class" line="113" lineend="272" name="HTML_TreeNode"><variable citdl="string" doc="The text for this node.&#10;@var string" line="119" name="text" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The link for this node.&#10;@var string" line="125" name="link" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The icon for this node.&#10;@var string" line="131" name="icon" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The css class for this node&#10;@var string" line="137" name="cssClass" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Indexed array of subnodes&#10;@var array" line="143" name="items" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Whether this node is expanded or not&#10;@var bool" line="149" name="expanded" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Whether this node is dynamic or not&#10;@var bool" line="155" name="isDynamic" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Should this node be made visible?&#10;@var bool" line="161" name="ensureVisible" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Javascript event handlers;&#10;@var array" line="173" name="events" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param  array $options An array of options which you can pass to change&#10;                       the way this node looks/acts. This can consist of:&#10;                        o text          The title of the node, defaults to blank&#10;                        o link          The link for the node, defaults to blank&#10;                        o icon          The icon for the node, defaults to blank&#10;                        o class         The CSS class for this node, defaults to blank&#10;                        o expanded      The default expanded status of this node, defaults to false&#10;                                        This doesn't affect non dynamic presentation types&#10;                        o isDynamic     If this node is dynamic or not. Only affects&#10;                                        certain presentation types.&#10;                        o ensureVisible If true this node will be made visible despite the expanded&#10;                                        settings, and client side persistence. Will not affect&#10;                                        some presentation styles, such as Listbox. Default is false&#10;@param  array $events An array of javascript events and the corresponding event handlers.&#10;                      Additionally to the standard javascript events you can specify handlers&#10;                      for the 'onexpand', 'oncollapse' and 'ontoggle' events which will be fired&#10;                      whenever a node is collapsed and/or expanded." ilk="function" line="197" lineend="213" name="HTML_TreeNode" signature="HTML_TreeNode(array $options = array(), array $events = array())"><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="197" name="options" /><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="197" name="events" /><variable line="210" name="option" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="210" name="value" /></scope><scope doc="Allows setting of various parameters after the initial&#10;constructor call. Possible options you can set are:&#10; o text&#10; o link&#10; o icon&#10; o cssClass&#10; o expanded&#10; o isDynamic&#10; o ensureVisible&#10;ie The same options as in the constructor&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param  string $option Option to set&#10;@param  string $value  Value to set the option to" ilk="function" line="231" lineend="234" name="setOption" signature="setOption(string $option, string $value)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="231" name="option" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="231" name="value" /></scope><scope doc="Adds a new subnode to this node.&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param  object $node The new node" ilk="function" line="242" lineend="256" name="addItem" returns="this.items" signature="&amp;addItem(object &amp; $node)"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="242" name="node" /></scope><scope doc="Private function to handle ensureVisible stuff&#10;&#10;@access private" ilk="function" line="263" lineend="271" name="_ensureVisible" signature="_ensureVisible()" /></scope><scope doc="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation class&#10;&#10;Base class for other presentation classes to&#10;inherit from.&#10;@package HTML_TreeMenu" ilk="class" line="282" lineend="318" name="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation"><variable citdl="structure" doc="The TreeMenu structure&#10;@var object" line="288" name="menu" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Base constructor simply sets the menu object&#10;&#10;@param object $structure The menu structure" ilk="function" line="295" lineend="298" name="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation" signature="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation(object &amp; $structure)"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="295" name="structure" /></scope><scope doc="Prints the HTML generated by the toHTML() method.&#10;toHTML() must therefore be defined by the derived&#10;class.&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param  array  Options to set. Any options taken by&#10;               the presentation class can be specified&#10;               here." ilk="function" line="310" lineend="317" name="printMenu" signature="printMenu($options = array())"><variable default="array()" ilk="argument" line="310" name="options" /><variable line="312" name="option" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="312" name="value" /></scope></scope><scope classrefs="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation" doc="HTML_TreeMenu_DHTML class&#10;&#10;This class is a presentation class for the tree structure&#10;created using the TreeMenu/TreeNode. It presents the &#10;traditional tree, static for browsers that can't handle&#10;the DHTML.&#10;@package HTML_TreeMenu" ilk="class" line="329" lineend="484" name="HTML_TreeMenu_DHTML"><variable citdl="isDynamic" line="336" name="isDynamic" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Path to the images&#10;@var string" line="342" name="images" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Target for the links generated&#10;@var string" line="348" name="linkTarget" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Whether to use clientside persistence or not&#10;@var bool" line="354" name="userPersistence" /><variable citdl="string" line="359" name="defaultClass" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Whether to skip first level branch images&#10;@var bool" line="365" name="noTopLevelImages" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor, takes the tree structure as&#10;an argument and an array of options which&#10;can consist of:&#10; o images            -  The path to the images folder. Defaults to &quot;images&quot;&#10; o linkTarget        -  The target for the link. Defaults to &quot;_self&quot;&#10; o defaultClass      -  The default CSS class to apply to a node. Default is none.&#10; o usePersistence    -  Whether to use clientside persistence. This persistence&#10;                        is achieved using cookies. Default is true.&#10; o noTopLevelImages  -  Whether to skip displaying the first level of images if&#10;                        there is multiple top level branches.&#10;&#10;And also a boolean for whether the entire tree is dynamic or not.&#10;This overrides any perNode dynamic settings.&#10;&#10;@param object $structure The menu structure&#10;@param array  $options   Array of options&#10;@param bool   $isDynamic Whether the tree is dynamic or not" ilk="function" line="386" lineend="401" name="HTML_TreeMenu_DHTML" signature="HTML_TreeMenu_DHTML(object &amp; $structure, array $options = array(), bool $isDynamic = true)"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="386" name="structure" /><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="386" name="options" /><variable citdl="bool" default="true" ilk="argument" line="386" name="isDynamic" /><variable line="398" name="option" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="398" name="value" /></scope><variable citdl="structure" line="388" name="menu" /><variable citdl="boolean" line="395" name="usePersistence" /><scope doc="Returns the HTML for the menu. This method can be&#10;used instead of printMenu() to use the menu system&#10;with a template system.&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@return string The HTML for the menu" ilk="function" line="411" lineend="445" name="toHTML" returns="string" signature="string toHTML()"><variable citdl="string" line="416" name="html" /><variable line="433" name="i" /><variable citdl="string" line="414" name="menuObj" /></scope><variable attributes="static" citdl="int" line="413" name="count" /><variable line="425" name="menuObj" /><scope doc="Prints a node of the menu&#10;&#10;@access private" ilk="function" line="452" lineend="483" name="_nodeToHTML" returns="html" signature="_nodeToHTML($nodeObj, $prefix, $return = 'newNode')"><variable ilk="argument" line="452" name="nodeObj" /><variable ilk="argument" line="452" name="prefix" /><variable default="'newNode'" ilk="argument" line="452" name="return" /><variable citdl="this.isDynamic" line="454" name="expanded" /><variable line="477" name="i" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="466" name="handler" /><variable line="466" name="event" /><variable citdl="sprintf()" line="464" name="html" /><variable citdl="this.isDynamic" line="455" name="isDynamic" /></scope></scope><scope classrefs="HTML_TreeMenu_Presentation" doc="HTML_TreeMenu_Listbox class&#10;&#10;This class presents the menu as a listbox&#10;@package HTML_TreeMenu" ilk="class" line="493" lineend="596" name="HTML_TreeMenu_Listbox"><variable citdl="string" doc="The text that is displayed in the first option&#10;@var string" line="499" name="promoText" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The character used for indentation&#10;@var string" line="505" name="indentChar" /><variable citdl="integer" doc="How many of the indent chars to use&#10;per indentation level&#10;@var integer" line="512" name="indentNum" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Target for the links generated&#10;@var string" line="518" name="linkTarget" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor&#10;&#10;@param object $structure The menu structure&#10;@param array  $options   Options whic affect the display of the listbox.&#10;                         These can consist of:&#10;                          o promoText  The text that appears at the the top of the listbox&#10;                                       Defaults to &quot;Select...&quot;&#10;                          o indentChar The character to use for indenting the nodes&#10;                                       Defaults to &quot;&amp;nbsp;&quot;&#10;                          o indentNum  How many of the indentChars to use per indentation level&#10;                                       Defaults to 2&#10;                          o linkTarget Target for the links. Defaults to &quot;_self&quot;&#10;                          o submitText Text for the submit button. Defaults to &quot;Go&quot;" ilk="function" line="535" lineend="547" name="HTML_TreeMenu_Listbox" signature="HTML_TreeMenu_Listbox(object $structure, array $options = array())"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="535" name="structure" /><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="535" name="options" /><variable line="544" name="option" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="544" name="value" /></scope><variable citdl="structure" line="537" name="menu" /><variable citdl="string" line="542" name="submitText" /><scope doc="Returns the HTML generated" ilk="function" line="552" lineend="574" name="toHTML" returns="sprintf()" signature="toHTML()"><variable line="561" name="i" /><variable citdl="string" line="555" name="nodeHTML" /></scope><variable attributes="static" citdl="int" line="554" name="count" /><scope doc="Returns HTML for a single node&#10;&#10;@access private" ilk="function" line="581" lineend="595" name="_nodeToHTML" returns="html" signature="_nodeToHTML($node, $prefix = '')"><variable ilk="argument" line="581" name="node" /><variable default="''" ilk="argument" line="581" name="prefix" /><variable line="589" name="i" /><variable citdl="sprintf()" line="583" name="html" /></scope></scope></scope>